metaData.descriptionCS: For picture items, the child names pictures that are displayed on the Client Device. For verbal items, the child gives definitions for words that the examiner reads aloud.

questions.title: †Item 5. Soap
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Remove the Client Device from the child’s view before administering verbal items.

To introduce the verbal items, say, I am going to say some words. Listen carefully and tell me what each word means.

SOAP. What is soap?

answers.html: Things are (gross, yucky, smelly) without it
Use it with water; [No reference to clean]
